# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the values are
#   specific to the developer's local machine and some commands like `pipenv` or `poetry`
#   might require custom variables.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if the platform is different, locking might fail.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains exact version locked for dependencies.
#   For application, commit poetry.lock. For library, ignore poetry.lock.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains exact version locked for dependencies.
# pdm.lock
#   pdm local configuration
.pdm-python
.pdm-build/

